02:45.861 --> 02:47.950
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:48.080 --> 02:49.430
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:49.560 --> 02:51.693
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR

02:51.823 --> 02:53.695
♪ NO DON'T YOU FEAR

02:53.825 --> 02:56.219
♪ I'LL BE READY

02:56.828 --> 02:59.701
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS ♪

03:00.354 --> 03:03.183
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

03:03.313 --> 03:07.012
[ROCK MUSIC]

03:21.679 --> 03:22.593
--HEY.

03:23.246 --> 03:24.204
-HEY.

03:26.423 --> 03:27.250
-CODY, RIGHT?

03:27.859 --> 03:29.121
-RIGHT.

03:29.644 --> 03:32.342
-SOUNDS LIKE THE HERO OF
AN AMERICAN COWBOY FLICK.

03:33.474 --> 03:35.084
I WAS THINKING ABOUT A SWIM.

03:35.824 --> 03:37.129
-WELL IT IS A NICE
EVENING FOR IT.

03:39.436 --> 03:40.524
-COME ON.

03:43.527 --> 03:44.441
-YEAH.

03:45.050 --> 03:48.532
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

04:41.846 --> 04:45.285
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

04:50.812 --> 04:52.379
[BEEPING]

04:53.510 --> 04:58.515
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

05:13.748 --> 05:14.575
[SMOOCHES]

05:18.448 --> 05:21.495
[GLASSES CLINKING]

05:25.629 --> 05:28.284
-ANOTHER PLACE, ANOTHER TIME.

05:30.721 --> 05:35.770
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

05:46.911 --> 05:51.351
[SOMBER MUSIC]

05:57.618 --> 06:00.490
-I WON'T LEAVE

06:01.099 --> 06:04.015
AND YOU CAN'T MAKE ME.

06:06.322 --> 06:11.153
[SOMBER MUSIC]

06:14.025 --> 06:14.983
LET'S GO.

06:18.813 --> 06:20.989
[DOG BARKING]

06:22.947 --> 06:27.387
[SOMBER MUSIC]

06:35.569 --> 06:37.048
-HEY MITCH, IT'S ALEX!

06:37.179 --> 06:39.007
EVERYONE'S DOWNSTAIRS,
I GOT A CUP OF COFFEE.

06:39.137 --> 06:40.704
-ALRIGHT, HOLD ON.

06:44.578 --> 06:45.361
-HEY.

06:45.492 --> 06:46.362
-HEY.

06:50.932 --> 06:52.237
-DID YOU EVEN GO
TO BED LAST NIGHT?

06:52.368 --> 06:53.282
-WHAT?

06:54.892 --> 06:57.939
-OH, I GUESS YOU DID.

06:59.767 --> 07:00.681
-WHAT THE HELL'S GOING ON?

07:00.811 --> 07:02.509
-I'LL SEE YOU DOWNSTAIRS.

07:02.639 --> 07:03.901
-WAIT A MINUTE, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT A MINUTE.

07:04.032 --> 07:04.946
NOTHING HAPPENED,
NOTHING HAPPENED.

07:05.076 --> 07:06.861
ALEX, ALEX, NOTHING HAPPENED!

07:06.991 --> 07:07.992
[ELEVATOR DINGS]

07:08.863 --> 07:11.909
OH, GREAT, OH, OH.

07:14.564 --> 07:16.261
GOOD MORNING LADIES,
WELCOME TO STAR CITY.

07:16.392 --> 07:17.219
[WOMEN LAUGHING]

07:17.349 --> 07:19.743
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

07:20.918 --> 07:24.444
[GRUNTING]

07:32.408 --> 07:35.933
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

07:42.157 --> 07:47.684
[BOAT HORN BLOWING]

07:47.815 --> 07:51.775
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

07:59.348 --> 08:02.133
[PEOPLE TALKING]

08:02.830 --> 08:03.744
ALEX.

08:04.396 --> 08:05.615
-I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT, OKAY?

08:05.746 --> 08:06.790
-ALEX, NOTHING HAPPENED.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.139
-GOOD MORNING, MITCH.

08:08.270 --> 08:10.185
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL MORNING.

08:10.794 --> 08:12.753
-NOTHING HAPPENED, RIGHT.

08:12.883 --> 08:14.798
-WELL WHAT IF IT DID ANYWAY.
I MEAN, FOR GOD'S SAKES,

08:14.929 --> 08:16.757
WE'RE NOT DATING HERE,
WE'RE STRICT...

08:17.409 --> 08:18.454
WAIT A MINUTE.

08:20.717 --> 08:21.805
ARE YOU JEALOUS?

08:21.936 --> 08:22.893
-OF WHAT?

08:23.024 --> 08:24.373
-OF ME BEING WITH A GIRL.

08:24.982 --> 08:27.550
-PLEASE, MY FEELINGS
FOR YOU ARE STRICTLY

08:27.681 --> 08:29.204
AS A FRIEND, OKAY?

08:29.334 --> 08:30.205
SEE YOU LATER.

08:31.206 --> 08:33.687
-HEY, WILD NIGHT, HUH?

08:33.817 --> 08:37.038
-ANNOUNCER: THE FIRST EVER
PAUL MITCHELL SYDNEY CHALLENGE.

08:37.168 --> 08:40.171
ALL COMPETITORS PLEASE
REPORT TO THE FIRST COURSE

08:40.302 --> 08:42.130
FOR YOUR FINAL
RACE INSTRUCTIONS.

08:42.783 --> 08:44.480
-10 MINUTES UNTIL STARTING.

08:47.527 --> 08:48.310
-HEY!

08:48.440 --> 08:49.224
-HEY, HOW ARE YOU?

08:49.354 --> 08:50.747
-GOOD.

08:50.878 --> 08:51.792
-HOPE I DIDN'T KEEP YOU
OUT TOO LATE LAST NIGHT.

08:51.922 --> 08:52.880
-ARE YOU KIDDING?

08:53.010 --> 08:53.794
I HAD A GREAT NIGHT.

08:53.924 --> 08:54.751
-YEAH?

08:54.882 --> 08:56.623
-I DID.

08:56.753 --> 08:58.842
-I'M GLAD YOUR MOM'S A BIG
BELIEVER IN THE BUDDY SYSTEM.

08:58.973 --> 09:00.365
[LAUGHING]

09:00.496 --> 09:01.541
-SHE GIVES ME SOME
GOOD ADVICE SOMETIMES.

09:01.671 --> 09:03.064
-YEAH, SHE DOES.

09:03.194 --> 09:06.284
-WOW, YOU LOOK
GREAT IN COSSIES,

09:06.415 --> 09:07.764
BUT I KNEW YOU WOULD.

09:07.895 --> 09:10.811
-THANKS, WHAT ARE COSSIES?

09:10.941 --> 09:12.247
-YOU KNOW.

09:12.377 --> 09:15.163
-OH, THANKS, YOU
LOOK GOOD YOURSELF.

09:15.293 --> 09:16.904
-THANKS, GOOD LUCK TODAY.

09:17.034 --> 09:18.079
-YOU, TOO.

09:19.428 --> 09:23.475
-ANNOUNCER: WELCOME TO THE
PAUL MITCHELL SYDNEY CHALLENGE.

09:23.606 --> 09:29.133
TEAM NIGHTWATCH USA AGAINST
TEAM SYDNEY AUSTRALIA.

09:29.743 --> 09:34.312
THIS IS A STAGED RACE.
PADDLE, RUN, SWIM.

09:34.443 --> 09:37.968
A LITTLE SURPRISE,
THEN MORE OF THE SAME.

09:38.099 --> 09:39.666
[GUN SHOT RINGS]

09:41.189 --> 09:44.018
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

09:49.327 --> 09:54.202
-KIP: LET'S GO, PADDLE,
LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT.

09:54.942 --> 09:56.073
KEEP PUSHING, GO!

09:56.204 --> 09:59.250
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

09:59.381 --> 10:00.904
-CODY: GO, GO, GO!

10:02.079 --> 10:05.082
-KIP: RIGHT,
LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT.

10:06.301 --> 10:08.738
-COME ON, LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT.

10:10.305 --> 10:11.088
-NICE AND SMOOTH.

10:11.219 --> 10:12.220
-OKAY.

10:13.177 --> 10:14.918
[RACING MUSIC]

10:19.183 --> 10:20.228
[DOOR KNOCKING]

10:20.358 --> 10:21.969
-HEY, YOU GONNA SLEEP ALL DAY?

10:26.626 --> 10:29.150
[SORROWFUL MUSIC]

10:29.280 --> 10:31.805
I WON'T LEAVE,
YOU CAN'T MAKE ME.

10:33.458 --> 10:37.637
[SORROWFUL MUSIC]

10:40.552 --> 10:43.991
-KIP: COME ON, RIGHT,
LEFT, RIGHT, RIGHT.

10:44.121 --> 10:48.212
RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT, RIGHT.

10:49.518 --> 10:51.215
[RACING MUSIC]

10:51.346 --> 10:54.784
NICE AND SMOOTH,
THAT A GIRL, THAT A GIRL.

10:55.393 --> 10:57.569
-ALEX, YOU'RE GONNA
WEAR YOURSELF OUT.

10:58.353 --> 11:00.485
-WOULD YOU PLEASE
STOP TALKING TO ME.

11:00.616 --> 11:02.531
-FOR GOD'S SAKES,
WHAT IS THE PROBLEM?

11:02.662 --> 11:06.361
-I DON'T KNOW, BUT WE HAVE
ONE, SO JUST STOP TALKING!

11:06.491 --> 11:09.277
-ALRIGHT, RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT.

11:10.887 --> 11:12.454
GET 'EM!

11:12.584 --> 11:14.891
-I UH, THINK I STIRRED
THE POT A LITTLE TOO MUCH.

11:15.022 --> 11:17.677
-YOU DID GREAT, THEY'VE
BEEN SCRAPPING ALL MORNING.

11:18.547 --> 11:19.591
-I LIKE HIM.

11:19.722 --> 11:21.898
-ALEX NOW, SHE'S
A REAL STUNNER.

11:22.029 --> 11:23.683
-MAYBE WE SHOULD LET THEM WIN.

11:23.813 --> 11:25.293
-YOU THINK?

11:25.423 --> 11:27.687
-ON SECOND THOUGHT,
LET'S HAMMER THEM,

11:27.817 --> 11:29.297
THEN LAY ON THE COMMISERATING.

11:29.427 --> 11:32.126
-YEAH, THAT COULD WORK.

11:32.256 --> 11:34.998
-NOTHING LIKE HELPING THE
ENEMY LICK THEIR WOUNDS.

11:35.129 --> 11:36.696
-YEAH, YOU BETCHA.

11:37.305 --> 11:40.438
-MITCH: RIGHT, LEFT,
RIGHT, LEFT.

11:41.613 --> 11:44.094
NICE. NICE AND SMOOTH.

11:44.225 --> 11:49.273
[RACING MUSIC]

11:52.059 --> 11:53.538
-HEY, WHAT ARE
THOSE FENCES FOR?

11:54.191 --> 11:55.062
-SHARKS.

11:55.584 --> 11:56.890
-SHARKS?

11:57.020 --> 11:58.630
-YEAH, SO THE
PEOPLE DON'T SWIM OUT

11:58.761 --> 11:59.719
AND BOTHER THE SHARKS.

11:59.849 --> 12:01.851
-HA HA, VERY FUNNY.

12:02.417 --> 12:04.680
BY THE WAY, WHERE DID YOU
DISAPPEAR TO LAST NIGHT?

12:05.376 --> 12:06.508
-OH, JUST WENT FOR A SWIM.

12:07.030 --> 12:08.902
-I HOPE YOU DIDN'T
WEAR YOURSELF OUT.

12:09.032 --> 12:12.383
-NO, NO, ACTUALLY,
IT WAS QUITE RELAXING.

12:14.777 --> 12:18.128
[RACING MUSIC]

12:18.781 --> 12:20.130
-YOU KNOW WHAT I
LIKE BEST ABOUT THEM?

12:20.261 --> 12:21.479
-I'M NOT SURE I WANT TO KNOW.

12:21.610 --> 12:23.394
-TUGGO, THEIR ACCENTS.

12:23.525 --> 12:24.613
-I'LL GIVE YOU THAT.

12:25.309 --> 12:26.354
THEY ARE SEXY.

12:26.484 --> 12:27.529
-OH, YEAH.

12:30.662 --> 12:31.794
-COME ON NICKIE.

12:34.928 --> 12:39.323
COME ON.
LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT, LEFT.

12:43.284 --> 12:45.460
-LEFT, DIG, COME ON, DIG!

12:45.590 --> 12:46.983
-I'M DIGGING.

12:47.114 --> 12:49.769
-DIG DEEPER! [GROANING]

12:51.031 --> 12:53.337
-PASSING US,
THEY'RE PASSING US!

12:53.468 --> 12:56.993
-HERE WE GO, LEFT,
RIGHT, LEFT, RIGHT.
COME ON, ALEX!

12:59.343 --> 13:03.434
[RACING MUSIC]

13:14.228 --> 13:15.185
-COME ON, CODY!

13:16.099 --> 13:17.622
-ALEX, GO, GO, GO!

13:17.753 --> 13:20.974
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

13:21.539 --> 13:23.454
-ALRIGHT, WE GOTTA GET THE MAP.

13:24.847 --> 13:26.588
YOU GOT IT, CODY?

13:26.718 --> 13:28.285
-WE SHOULD KNOW WHERE WE'RE
GOING, BUT I'VE GOT NO IDEA.

13:28.416 --> 13:30.635
-MITCH: COME ON ALEX,
LET'S GO, LET'S GO, GO, GO!

13:30.766 --> 13:32.115
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

13:33.943 --> 13:35.597
[GASPING]

13:36.903 --> 13:38.165
-YOU GOT IT, CODY?

13:38.295 --> 13:39.514
-ALRIGHT, I GOT
IT, STRAIGHT AHEAD,

13:39.644 --> 13:40.776
BEHIND THOSE TREES, LET'S GO!

13:41.777 --> 13:43.561
-MITCH: ALRIGHT, YOU GUYS,
WE SHOULD BE REALLY FAST HERE.

13:43.692 --> 13:47.000
-CODY: COME ON, LET'S
GO, LET'S GO, LET'S GO.

13:47.130 --> 13:48.740
-HURRY UP, GO!

13:50.960 --> 13:54.007
[EVERYONE CHEERING]

13:54.137 --> 13:56.879
[CAMERA'S CLICKING]

14:00.317 --> 14:01.492
-AND THEN THESE ON THE CLIFF.

14:02.319 --> 14:03.712
FANTASTIC HOUSES.

14:03.843 --> 14:04.756
-WOW.

14:04.887 --> 14:05.714
-YEP, PRETTY AMAZING.

14:05.845 --> 14:06.889
-SO BEAUTIFUL.

14:07.977 --> 14:10.284
-RENE, I HAVE SOMEONE
I'D LIKE YOU TO MEET.

14:10.893 --> 14:11.720
JESSIE, THIS IS RENE RIVKIN.

14:11.851 --> 14:12.590
-PLEASED TO MEET YOU.

14:12.721 --> 14:13.678
-HI.

14:13.809 --> 14:14.636
-HE WAS A FRIEND OF CLARE'S.

14:14.766 --> 14:16.072
HE'S THE EXECUTOR OF HER ESTATE.

14:16.203 --> 14:17.421
-ESTATE?

14:17.552 --> 14:19.075
-A COUPLE OF HUNDRED IN CASH,

14:19.206 --> 14:21.208
PLUS ABOUT $12,000.00
IN THE CHECKING ACCOUNT.

14:21.773 --> 14:23.210
BUT IT IS ALL FOR TERRY.

14:23.340 --> 14:25.386
-I WOULDN'T EXACTLY CALL
$12,000.00 AN ESTATE.

14:25.516 --> 14:26.866
-I WOULDN'T EITHER,
BUT BY THE TIME

14:26.996 --> 14:29.216
I'M FINISHED INVESTING IT,
IT WILL BE.

14:29.346 --> 14:31.131
-REALLY?

14:31.261 --> 14:33.655
-ABSOLUTELY, BY THE TIME HE'S
25 HE'LL BE SET UP FOR LIFE.

14:34.438 --> 14:35.178
ALLIE, I HAVE TO GO.ALLU

14:35.309 --> 14:36.136
-OKAY.

14:36.266 --> 14:37.050
[SMOOCHES]

14:37.180 --> 14:38.529
SEE YOU.

14:38.660 --> 14:40.140
-JESSIE, IF THERE'S
ANYTHING I CAN DO FOR YOU,

14:40.270 --> 14:41.097
JUST FEEL FREE TO CALL.

14:41.228 --> 14:42.229
-THANKS.

14:42.359 --> 14:43.534
-SEE YOU.

14:46.189 --> 14:47.190
-JAKE!

14:48.104 --> 14:49.018
-TERRY'S RUN AWAY.

14:49.627 --> 14:51.064
-RUN AWAY?
WHY WOULD HE DO THAT?

14:51.194 --> 14:52.456
-I TOLD HIM I WAS
TAKING HIM BACK TO L.A.,

14:52.587 --> 14:53.936
AND HE DOESN'T WANT TO GO.

14:54.067 --> 14:55.459
RIGHT NOW DOES HE
HAVE ANY RELATIVES?

14:55.590 --> 14:56.765
-NO.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.201
-OKAY, WHAT ABOUT FRIENDS?

14:58.332 --> 14:59.159
YOU KNOW,
LIKE KIDS FROM THE BEACH?

14:59.289 --> 15:00.812
-I'LL HAVE TO MAKE SOME CALLS.

15:00.943 --> 15:02.205
-HE WANTS YOU TO FIND HIM.

15:02.336 --> 15:03.337
-HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT?

15:04.381 --> 15:05.643
-THE NOTE.

15:06.253 --> 15:08.864
IF YOU WANT TO GO AND STAY
GONE, YOU DON'T LEAVE A NOTE.

15:09.865 --> 15:12.085
TRUST ME, I KNOW FROM
PERSONAL EXPERIENCE.

15:12.694 --> 15:13.869
-CLARE WOULD KNOW
WHERE TO FIND HIM.

15:16.480 --> 15:18.526
-LOOK, ALL OF CLARE'S
STUFF IS IN A GARAGE

15:18.656 --> 15:20.006
ON SAINT ANNE'S BLUFF.

15:20.136 --> 15:21.398
WE MIGHT FIND SOMETHING THERE.

15:23.183 --> 15:28.057
[TECHNO MUSIC]

16:25.767 --> 16:28.378
[GASPING]

16:31.164 --> 16:32.513
-THAT'S WHERE WE GOTTA
GO, RIGHT OVER THERE.

16:32.643 --> 16:33.557
-MITCH: OKAY.

16:33.688 --> 16:34.906
-IT'S BEAUTIFUL, HUH?

16:35.037 --> 16:36.560
-MOST AWESOME ROCK
ON THE PLANET,

16:36.691 --> 16:38.171
AND CAPTION COOK SAY IT
RIGHT AND DRIVE, YOU IDIOT.

16:38.301 --> 16:39.215
[LAUGHING]

16:39.346 --> 16:40.129
-HOW DO WE GET OVER THERE?

16:40.260 --> 16:41.217
-ON THOSE.

16:44.351 --> 16:45.700
4O, GO, GO!

16:47.223 --> 16:48.485
-BLOND WOMAN: HOPE IT'S NICE!

16:50.531 --> 16:52.881
[LIVELY MUSIC]

17:00.541 --> 17:06.199
[STRINGS MUSIC]

17:07.503 --> 17:10.507
[GASPING]

17:18.819 --> 17:23.954
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

17:30.353 --> 17:32.660
[GRUNTING]

17:42.148 --> 17:44.628
[SCREAMING]

17:46.674 --> 17:47.631
-HEY!

17:48.980 --> 17:49.894
HANG ON!

17:50.025 --> 17:50.721
-KIP: CAN YOU GET TO HER?

17:50.852 --> 17:51.983
-I THINK SO.

17:53.115 --> 17:54.073
YOU HURT?

17:54.682 --> 17:56.075
-I'M ALRIGHT.

17:56.205 --> 17:58.599
-SHE'S HUNG UP,
CAN YOU HOLD HER?

17:59.382 --> 18:00.296
-HERE, GRAB MY HAND.

18:02.255 --> 18:03.430
OKAY, I GOT HER!

18:03.560 --> 18:05.214
-OK.

18:05.345 --> 18:06.520
-ALRIGHT, NICKIE, MITCH
IS GONNA HANG ON TO YOU

18:06.650 --> 18:08.217
AND I'M GONNA
UNTANGLE YOU, OKAY?

18:08.348 --> 18:09.566
-YEAH.

18:10.785 --> 18:12.439
[MOANING]

18:16.356 --> 18:18.314
-OKAY, PULL HER UP.

18:18.880 --> 18:19.750
-I DON'T THINK I CAN.

18:19.881 --> 18:20.969
-WHAT?

18:21.100 --> 18:22.188
-WELL YOU GRABBED MY WEAK HAND.

18:22.971 --> 18:24.799
-YOUR WEAK HAND?

18:24.929 --> 18:26.583
-ALEX, YOU KNOW HOW WEAK
MY LEFT HAND IS, DON'T YOU?

18:27.715 --> 18:28.759
-WHAT DO YOU NEED?

18:28.890 --> 18:31.110
-NOTHING, I THINK I GOT HER.

18:31.240 --> 18:32.154
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN, "YOU THINK?"

18:32.285 --> 18:34.374
EITHER YOU HAVE
HER OR YOU DON'T.

18:34.504 --> 18:36.245
-WELL, IT'S KIND OF LIKE
LAST NIGHT, ISN'T IT, NICKIE?

18:36.376 --> 18:38.421
I REALLY DON'T THINK
ANYTHING HAPPENED,

18:38.552 --> 18:40.206
BUT I'M NOT REALLY SURE.

18:40.771 --> 18:42.730
-PULL ME UP, THIS ISN'T FUNNY!

18:42.860 --> 18:44.471
-AM I LAUGHING,
ALEX, AM I LAUGHING?

18:44.601 --> 18:46.821
-NO, NO, YOU WEREN'T
LAUGHING AT ALL.

18:46.951 --> 18:48.257
-NOW, I THINK YOU SET ME UP.

18:48.388 --> 18:49.867
YOU WANT TO TELL
HER WHAT HAPPENED?

18:49.998 --> 18:51.391
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

18:51.521 --> 18:56.265
-OH! OH, I'M CRAMPING,
OH, NOT AGAIN!

18:56.396 --> 18:58.180
I HATE WHEN THAT HAPPENS.

18:58.311 --> 19:00.661
-ALEX: OH, GOD, IT ALWAYS
HAPPENS AT THE WORST TIMES, TOO.

19:00.791 --> 19:01.575
DOESN'T IT?

19:01.705 --> 19:02.532
-PULL ME UP!

19:03.316 --> 19:05.100
-TELL HER NOTHING HAPPENED.

19:06.145 --> 19:07.146
-CODY: WHAT'S THE HOLD UP?

19:07.798 --> 19:08.843
NOTHING HAPPENED.

19:08.973 --> 19:09.931
-I DIDN'T HEAR THAT,
DID YOU HEAR THAT?

19:10.061 --> 19:10.975
-NO.

19:11.106 --> 19:12.412
-SHE DIDN'T HEAR YOU.

19:12.542 --> 19:13.978
-NOTHING HAPPENED!

19:14.109 --> 19:15.241
-NOTHING HAPPENED!

19:16.111 --> 19:17.504
AND WHY THE SILLY GAME?

19:17.634 --> 19:19.332
-IT WAS KIP'S IDEA.

19:19.462 --> 19:21.160
HE THOUGHT IT WOULD
CREATE DISSENSION,

19:21.290 --> 19:23.162
GET YOU FIGHTING AND
PUT YOU OFF YOUR GAME.

19:23.292 --> 19:24.728
-IT WAS A STUPID IDEA.

19:24.859 --> 19:27.905
I'M SORRY, IT
WAS A STUPID IDEA.

19:29.255 --> 19:30.778
-ALRIGHT, PULL HER UP.

19:34.738 --> 19:35.870
-MITCH: THERE YOU GO.

19:38.046 --> 19:43.051
[LIVELY MUSIC]

19:49.884 --> 19:51.451
-IS EVERYTHING ALRIGHT?

19:51.581 --> 19:53.453
-I NICKED MY PRIDE, BUT
OTHERWISE I'M FINE, THANKS.

19:53.583 --> 19:55.106
-WOO, THAT WAS CLOSE.

19:55.237 --> 19:56.238
-KIP!

19:56.369 --> 19:58.109
-WHAT IS IT?

19:58.240 --> 20:00.286
-THERE'S A KID IN TROUBLE
BACK AT PORT DENISON.

20:00.416 --> 20:02.636
NO ONE ELSE CAN GET
THERE, WE NEED YOUR HELP.

20:02.766 --> 20:03.898
-WE'RE ON IT.

20:07.597 --> 20:09.469
-EVERYTHING THAT
CLARE SAVED IS IN HERE.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.912
-YOURS?

20:18.042 --> 20:20.480
-YEAH, I WOULD HAVE THOUGHT
CLARE HAD SOLD IT BY NOW.

20:21.611 --> 20:23.222
-LOOKS LIKE IT HASN'T
BEEN DRIVEN IN AWHILE.

20:23.352 --> 20:26.007
-IT HASN'T. IT HASN'T
BEEN DRIVEN SINCE YOU LEFT.

20:36.844 --> 20:37.801
-OH.

20:40.151 --> 20:41.718
THIS IS WHERE I FIRST MET HER.

20:42.676 --> 20:45.722
GOD, I NEVER MET A GIRL
SO HUNGRY FOR LIFE.

20:45.853 --> 20:47.420
I MEAN, SHE JUST
WANTED TO GOBBLE IT UP.

20:49.117 --> 20:50.901
FROM THE MOMENT THAT
I FIRST MET HER,

20:51.989 --> 20:53.469
I THOUGHT LIFE COULDN'T
GET ANY BETTER.

20:57.299 --> 20:58.648
THEN IT ALL CHANGED.

20:58.779 --> 21:00.607
-BECAUSE SHE GOT PREGNANT?

21:01.999 --> 21:03.392
-I DIDN'T KNOW THAT.

21:04.567 --> 21:06.743
ALL I KNEW WAS THAT SHE WANTED
TO SPEND MORE TIME ALONE.

21:07.570 --> 21:08.963
-SHE WAS TRYING TO
FIGURE OUT HOW TO DEAL

21:09.093 --> 21:11.574
WITH WANTING THIS
BABY AND WANTING YOU.

21:11.705 --> 21:12.923
-YEAH, WELL SHE
FIGURED THAT OUT.

21:14.011 --> 21:15.404
DUMP OLD JAKE.

21:20.322 --> 21:21.715
WRITTEN BUT NOT SENT.

21:30.245 --> 21:33.727
[SOLEMN MUSIC]

21:35.250 --> 21:38.166
DEAREST JAKE, THIS IS THE
MOST DIFFICULT DECISION

21:38.297 --> 21:40.734
OF MY LIFE. BUT I KNOW
IT'S THE RIGHT ONE.

21:42.257 --> 21:43.650
-CLARE: I MUST LET YOU GO.

21:44.912 --> 21:46.783
I LET YOU GO BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.

21:47.480 --> 21:50.396
I LET YOU GO BECAUSE
YOU STILL NEED TO SOAR.

21:51.658 --> 21:55.314
TO FIGHT THE SUN AND
CONQUER THE SEAS.

21:57.881 --> 22:02.277
I LET YOU GO WITH THE HOPE
THAT ONE DAY YOU WILL RETURN.

22:04.192 --> 22:06.455
I BELIEVE WITH ALL OF
MY HEART THAT YOU WILL.

22:09.371 --> 22:11.721
THERE ARE THINGS WHICH
I CANNOT TELL YOU,

22:11.852 --> 22:14.202
BECAUSE I KNOW IT WILL
CHANGE EVERYTHING.

22:15.899 --> 22:20.730
IF I REVEAL MY SECRET, YOU
WILL BE OBLIGED TO STAY.

22:21.688 --> 22:22.950
I CANNOT ALLOW THAT.

22:25.300 --> 22:29.217
SO GO, GO, CHASE YOUR WILDNESS.

22:30.523 --> 22:33.569
AND WHEN YOU ARE
DONE, COME BACK.

22:35.484 --> 22:36.964
WE'LL BE WAITING.

22:38.792 --> 22:44.014
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

22:46.277 --> 22:48.584
[LAUGHING]

22:50.673 --> 22:55.809
[ROMANTIC MUSIC]

23:11.520 --> 23:12.739
-I NEVER KNEW.

23:14.784 --> 23:15.829
I BLEW IT.

23:19.485 --> 23:21.269
ALL I THINK ABOUT IS MYSELF.

23:25.316 --> 23:26.143
YOU KNEW THAT.

23:30.278 --> 23:34.021
YOU AND MITCH, THAT'S WHY YOU
TOLD ME IT'S TIME TO GROW UP.

23:37.241 --> 23:38.155
I HOPE IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

23:40.462 --> 23:41.681
DOES CLARE STILL HAVE A BOAT?

23:42.421 --> 23:44.118
-YEAH, A LITTLE SAILBOAT.

23:45.685 --> 23:47.556
-CAN YOU CALL UP AND SEE
IF TERRY'S TAKEN IT OUT?

23:51.734 --> 23:53.780
-HI, IT'S ALLIE, HAVE
YOU SEEN TERRY BARNES?

23:55.129 --> 23:56.260
HE SAYS HE HASN'T SEEN HIM.

23:56.391 --> 23:57.740
-ASK HIM IF THE
BOAT'S STILL THERE.

23:57.871 --> 23:59.176
-IS CLARE'S BOAT THERE?

24:01.178 --> 24:02.005
THE BOAT'S GONE.

24:02.136 --> 24:03.920
-TERRY'S GOT IT, I KNOW IT.

24:04.051 --> 24:05.444
-I'LL GET THE FLIGHT PLANE
AND SEARCH THE HARBOR.

24:05.574 --> 24:07.271
-I'M GONNA GO BACK TO
AVALON AND LOOK THERE.

24:07.402 --> 24:08.751
-YOU MAY NEED AN EXTRA PAIR
OF EYES, CAN I GO WITH YOU?

24:08.882 --> 24:10.231
-YEAH.

24:12.233 --> 24:17.107
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

24:19.327 --> 24:22.112
[WAVES SPLASHING]

24:24.550 --> 24:28.379
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

24:38.085 --> 24:43.699
[ENGINES SCREAMING]

24:47.747 --> 24:51.925
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

24:55.276 --> 24:59.280
[ENGINES SCREAMING]

25:03.414 --> 25:07.157
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

25:16.863 --> 25:17.820
-THERE SHE IS!

25:20.301 --> 25:25.349
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

25:26.916 --> 25:27.830
[SCREAMING]

25:27.961 --> 25:29.571
-ALEX: WHAT HAPPENED?

25:29.702 --> 25:31.225
-MOTHER: SHE WAS PLAYING
UNDER THE ROCKS AND GOT STUCK!

25:31.355 --> 25:32.618
[EVERYONE YELLING]

25:32.748 --> 25:33.444
-WE GOT HER, WE GOT HER,
COME ON FOLKS, LET'S GO.

25:33.575 --> 25:35.751
[EVERYONE TALKING]

25:35.882 --> 25:36.447
-ALEX: OKAY, ALRIGHT, WE'RE
GONNA GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

25:36.578 --> 25:37.361
-ALRIGHT, SHE'S PINNED.

25:37.492 --> 25:38.537
.WE GOTTA MOVE THIS ROCK.

25:38.667 --> 25:41.017
[EVERYONE TALKING]

25:41.148 --> 25:44.673
-OKAY, ON THREE, RIGHT
QUICK, ONE, TWO, THREE.

25:44.804 --> 25:46.283
[GROANING]

25:46.414 --> 25:47.763
OKAY, OKAY, ONE, TWO, THREE.

25:47.894 --> 25:49.069
[GROANING]

25:49.199 --> 25:50.723
-ONCE AGAIN.

25:50.853 --> 25:52.333
-ALRIGHT, LET'S GO, LET'S GO!

25:52.463 --> 25:53.203
-OKAY, LET'S GO,
ONE, TWO, THREE!

25:53.334 --> 25:54.465
[GROANING]

25:54.596 --> 25:55.597
-COME ON, COME ON,
ONE, TWO, THREE!

25:55.728 --> 25:56.555
[GROANING]

25:56.685 --> 25:57.468
WE NEED SOME LEVERAGE.

25:57.599 --> 25:58.600
-MITCH: ALRIGHT, WE'RE ON IT.

25:58.731 --> 25:59.732
-KIP: WHERE'S SOME ROPE.

25:59.862 --> 26:00.689
-MITCH, TIDES COMING IN, DUDE.

26:01.516 --> 26:03.083
WE'VE GOT ABOUT TWO MINUTES.

26:03.213 --> 26:05.085
-OKAY, ALRIGHT, WHAT'S
YOUR NAME, DARLING?

26:05.215 --> 26:06.042
-JAMIE.

26:06.173 --> 26:07.609
-JAMIE, OKAY, MY NAME IS MITCH.

26:07.740 --> 26:08.958
NOW YOU GOTTA TRUST ME,

26:09.089 --> 26:10.046
WE'RE GONNA GET THIS
ROCK OFF OF YOU.

26:12.092 --> 26:13.223
WHERE'S THAT ROPE, GUYS?

26:13.354 --> 26:14.964
-PLEASE, HELP ME.

26:15.095 --> 26:16.966
-LISTEN TO ME, WE'RE GONNA
GET YOU OUT OF HERE, OKAY?

26:17.097 --> 26:18.664
-APRIL: ALL THE WAY AROUND.

26:18.794 --> 26:20.013
-WE'RE GONNA GET YOU
OUT, YOU BETTER TRUST HIM, OKAY?

26:20.143 --> 26:21.275
OKAY.

26:21.405 --> 26:22.493
-APRIL: OKAY WE'RE
ON IT, COME ON.

26:22.624 --> 26:23.277
-ALRIGHT, GIVE US 10
SECONDS.

26:23.407 --> 26:24.495
-OKAY!

26:25.279 --> 26:29.413
[ENGINES SCREAMING]

26:35.115 --> 26:37.421
[GRUNTING]

26:38.640 --> 26:42.383
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

26:44.211 --> 26:47.823
[ENGINES SCREAMING]

26:47.954 --> 26:49.999
[ENERGETIC MUSIC]

26:50.130 --> 26:52.567
[ENGINES SCREAMING]

26:52.698 --> 26:54.264
-PULL HER OUT, GO!

26:55.396 --> 26:56.571
[GASPING]

26:58.573 --> 27:00.706
-MITCH: WE GOT HER,
WE GOT HER!

27:00.836 --> 27:03.273
[EVERYONE YELLING AND CHEERING]

27:03.404 --> 27:04.623
-YEAH!

27:06.146 --> 27:06.973
-KIP: WAY TO GO!

27:07.800 --> 27:08.888
-WAY TO GO!

27:09.018 --> 27:10.629
-WAY TO GO, YEAH!

27:14.676 --> 27:16.852
-WE'RE GONNA START WHERE
THE BOAT WAS DOCKED.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.854
THEN RUN A ZERO
POINT SEARCH PATTERN,

27:19.420 --> 27:21.509
AND DROP DOWN ON ANYTHING
THAT SEEMS LIKELY.

27:22.684 --> 27:26.645
[ENGINE WHIRRING]

27:30.779 --> 27:33.042
[BEATING MUSIC]

27:47.535 --> 27:50.016
[WAVES SPLASHING]

27:51.365 --> 27:55.935
[DOG WHINING]

28:01.418 --> 28:03.725
[ENGINE WHIRRING]

28:10.950 --> 28:11.907
-JAKE?

28:12.038 --> 28:13.256
-ALLIE, GO AHEAD.

28:13.387 --> 28:14.823
-WE'VE SPOTTED HIM.

28:14.954 --> 28:16.520
HE'S IN CLARE'S BOAT
JUST OFF DUNBAR BEACH.

28:16.651 --> 28:17.696
-JAKE: IS HE OKAY?

28:17.826 --> 28:19.567
-HE LOOKS FINE FROM HERE.

28:20.437 --> 28:22.831
-ALRIGHT, RADIO MITCH, TELL
HIM TO MEET ME AT THE DOCK.

28:22.962 --> 28:24.790
I'LL PICK HIM UP
IN THE IRV, OVER.

28:25.486 --> 28:26.443
-GOT IT.

28:28.968 --> 28:31.971
[LIVELY MUSIC]

28:36.410 --> 28:38.891
[ENGINE SCREAMING]

28:46.115 --> 28:47.116
-HEY.

28:47.856 --> 28:48.770
-WHERE IS HE?

28:49.684 --> 28:51.642
-HE'S OFF CRONDIKE
ABOUT FIVE MILES SOUTH.

28:51.773 --> 28:53.688
-ALRIGHT, LET'S GO, COME ON.

28:54.820 --> 28:57.561
[ENGINE SCREAMING]

29:03.002 --> 29:05.091
-OH NO, HE HAS TO TACK
AWAY FROM THOSE ROCKS.

29:06.222 --> 29:07.441
-I DON'T THINK HE SEES THEM.

29:14.317 --> 29:18.495
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

29:29.898 --> 29:30.986
JAKE, WHERE ARE YOU?

29:31.944 --> 29:32.988
-JAKE: JUST PASSING
THE SOUTH HEDLAND.

29:33.119 --> 29:34.511
WHY, WHAT IS IT?

29:34.642 --> 29:36.470
-HE'S ON THE ROCKS,
COME AS FAST AS YOU CAN.

29:39.386 --> 29:41.431
WESTPAC, THIS IS SS TWO BRAVO.

29:41.562 --> 29:43.216
WE'RE A MILE EAST OF TAMARAMA.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.131
WE NEED IMMEDIATE ASSISTANCE.

29:50.919 --> 29:54.009
[ENGINES WHIRRING]

29:55.794 --> 29:58.666
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

30:00.363 --> 30:03.062
[ENGINE SCREAMING]

30:03.714 --> 30:04.933
-THERE HE IS!

30:06.456 --> 30:07.718
WE GOTTA GET HIM OFF THAT BOAT.

30:07.849 --> 30:10.983
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

30:12.898 --> 30:16.553
[DOG WHINING]

30:16.684 --> 30:19.600
[ENGINE SCREAMING]

30:29.175 --> 30:30.567
-RADIO: GETTING
ON SCENE, THREE MINUTES.

30:32.047 --> 30:35.834
[CHOPPER WHIRRING]

30:41.013 --> 30:42.101
-WHERE'S HIS DOG?

30:42.928 --> 30:44.146
HE WON'T LEAVE WITHOUT HIM.

30:45.974 --> 30:47.019
-TERRY!

30:47.149 --> 30:49.760
[DOG WHINING]

30:49.891 --> 30:51.893
[SCREAMING]

30:52.024 --> 30:53.373
[SPLASHING]

30:53.503 --> 30:55.418
-[FRANTIC MUSIC]

31:03.513 --> 31:06.125
[WATER SPLASHING]

31:06.255 --> 31:10.956
[CHOPPER WHIRRING]

31:11.086 --> 31:13.001
[WATER SPLASHING]

31:13.132 --> 31:15.874
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

31:18.615 --> 31:19.878
TERRY!

31:24.447 --> 31:25.840
IT'S OKAY, BOSS.

31:25.971 --> 31:27.059
--I'VE GOTTA GET
BACK IN THE BOAT!

31:27.842 --> 31:29.191
-NO, NO, NO. COME ON, LET'S GO.

31:29.322 --> 31:30.801
-I'VE GOTTA GET SPENCER!

31:30.932 --> 31:31.846
-WHO'S SPENCER?

31:31.977 --> 31:32.891
-MY DOG!

31:33.543 --> 31:34.414
-WHAT'S WRONG?

31:34.544 --> 31:35.545
-HIS DOG'S STILL IN THE BOAT.

31:35.676 --> 31:36.677
-JAKE: I'LL GET HIM.

31:38.548 --> 31:41.464
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

31:46.730 --> 31:48.732
[DOG WHINING]

31:52.127 --> 31:53.389
-WHAT'S HE DOING?

31:55.000 --> 31:56.001
-JAKE'S GOING FOR THE DOG.

31:56.131 --> 31:57.176
-OH, THAT'S CRAZY.

31:58.481 --> 31:59.787
[DOG WHINING]

31:59.918 --> 32:01.876
[WATER SPLASHING]

32:04.574 --> 32:07.664
[CHOPPER WHIRRING]

32:09.144 --> 32:11.190
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

32:24.986 --> 32:29.034
[WATER SPLASHING]

32:29.991 --> 32:32.254
-[LAUGHING]

32:33.560 --> 32:35.431
-HE'S GOT SPENCER,
HE GOT MY DOG!

32:35.562 --> 32:37.912
-OF COURSE HE DID,
THAT'S YOUR DAD.

32:38.565 --> 32:42.873
[CHOPPER CHUGGING]

32:43.004 --> 32:44.963
[FRANTIC MUSIC]

32:45.093 --> 32:47.139
[CHOPPER CHUGGING]

32:47.269 --> 32:48.140
[GRUNTING]

33:11.380 --> 33:13.078
-GOOD DOG, YOU OKAY, SPENCE?

33:16.124 --> 33:17.386
WOO!

33:18.779 --> 33:20.911
-RESCUE: WESTPAC CHOPPER,
PREPARE TO HOIST.

33:22.783 --> 33:26.743
[CHOPPER CHUGGING]

33:28.354 --> 33:30.617
-IT'S OKAY, DO YOU LIKE THAT?

33:30.747 --> 33:32.271
GOOD DOG.
[SMOOCHES]

33:55.250 --> 33:58.297
[SOMBER MUSIC]

34:00.864 --> 34:05.347
[GENTLE PIANO MUSIC]

34:14.181 --> 34:15.531
IT'S ONLY US NOW.

34:17.359 --> 34:20.536
I PROMISE YOU, I'M
NEVER GONNA LEAVE YOU.

34:22.016 --> 34:24.409
NO MATTER WHAT WE DO,
NO MATTER WHERE WE GO.

34:25.063 --> 34:26.716
WE'RE GONNA DO IT
BECAUSE WE BOTH WANT TO.

34:27.935 --> 34:29.676
WE'VE GOT EIGHT YEARS
OF CATCHING UP TO DO.

34:30.677 --> 34:31.678
-SO WE'RE NOT LEAVING?

34:32.635 --> 34:33.853
-I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

34:35.551 --> 34:37.205
BUT WE WON'T LEAVE
UNLESS YOU WANT TO.

34:37.900 --> 34:42.254
BUT, I AM GONNA FILL YOUR
HEAD SO FULL OF CALIFORNIA,

34:42.949 --> 34:46.127
THE STORIES, THE MUSIC, YOU'RE
GONNA BE BEGGING ME TO GO.

34:46.780 --> 34:49.087
-AND I'LL SHOW YOU THAT
SYDNEY'S THE BEST PLACE TO BE,

34:49.217 --> 34:50.697
AND YOU WON'T WANT
TO LEAVE EVER.

34:51.437 --> 34:52.438
-THEN THAT'S THE DEAL.

34:52.568 --> 34:53.525
-OKAY.

34:53.656 --> 34:54.527
-OKAY.

35:02.622 --> 35:07.496
[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

35:08.280 --> 35:09.716
-TERRY: SO WHAT
KIND OF CAR IS IT?

35:09.846 --> 35:12.327
-THIS? THIS IS A BOSS RIDE.

35:13.502 --> 35:15.330
AND THIS IS YOUR FIRST
TASTE OF MY WORLD.

35:16.201 --> 35:20.379
IN CALIFORNIA, IT'S ALL
ABOUT THE SUN, SAND,

35:21.249 --> 35:26.080
THE SURF, FAST CARS,
AND HEARTS TO BREAK.

35:29.083 --> 35:32.086
[ENGINE CHUGGING]

35:41.095 --> 35:43.053
-TERRY: YOU KNOW
THE OLYMPICS ARE HERE IN 2000?

35:43.184 --> 35:44.881
-JAKE: YEAH,
YEAH, I HEARD THAT.

35:45.012 --> 35:46.274
-TERRY: IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

35:46.405 --> 35:47.406
-JAKE: WE SHOULD
GET SOME TICKETS.

35:47.536 --> 35:49.321
-TERRY: YEAH, ARE YOU HUNGRY?

35:49.451 --> 35:51.279
-JAKE: NOW THAT YOU MENTION
IT, YEAH, I'M STARVING.

35:52.150 --> 35:53.847
DO THEY HAVE AN IN AND
OUT BURGER AROUND HERE?

35:53.977 --> 35:55.196
-TERRY: A WHAT?

35:55.327 --> 35:56.719
-JAKE: IN AND OUT BURGER?

35:56.850 --> 35:58.460
YOU KNOW, DOUBLE,
DOUBLE CHEESE, FRIES,

35:58.591 --> 35:59.896
A COKE, A SHAKE MAYBE.

36:00.027 --> 36:01.115
-TERRY: [LAUGHING] NO.

36:01.246 --> 36:02.856
-JAKE: YOU ARE
SUCH [MUMBLING].

36:05.815 --> 36:09.167
[UPLIFTING MUSIC]

36:15.303 --> 36:16.739
-MAYBE WE'LL GET
EVERYONE TOGETHER LATER ON

36:16.870 --> 36:18.393
-AND TAKE THIS THING OUT.

36:18.524 --> 36:19.438
-YEAH, YEAH, WE'LL HAVE
A LITTLE BREAKFAST FIRST,

36:19.568 --> 36:20.221
IT'S A BIT HEAVY, YOU KNOW.

36:20.352 --> 36:21.179
-HEY!

36:21.875 --> 36:23.224
-WHERE IS EVERYONE?

